minister /ˈmɪnɪstə/

(ministers) 

1. N-COUNT A minister is a member of the clergy, especially in Protestant churches. 牧师 

例： His father was a Baptist minister. 他父亲是一名浸礼会牧师。 

2. N-COUNT A minister is a person who officially represents their government in a foreign country and has a lower rank than an ambassador. 公使 

例： He concluded a deal with the Danish minister in Washington. 他在华盛顿与丹麦公使达成了一项协议。 

3. N-COUNT In some countries outside the United States, a minister is a person who is in charge of a particular government department. 政府部门部长 

例： When the government came to power, he was named minister of culture. 这届政府上台时，他被任命为了文化部长。

